						<h2>Geography</h2>
						Mboro is administratively part of the region of Thies, and the department of Tivaoune.<br>
						The town is nested in northwestern Senegal nicknamed "la Grande côte". A vast coastline area following the Atlantic Ocean from Dakar to Saint Louis.
						The climate is mild most of the year, from October to June as the nearby sea plays a thermal regulator role. The diverse landscape is 
						characterized by a sharp cleavage that will meet different leisure needs. On the east, a succession of sandy dunes, some as high as 20 meters, 
						will give you a feeling of total change of scenery and an awesome playground to hiking enthusiasts.
						Towards the greener west of the town, a wide pristine forest of filao trees planted between the sea and arable lands to prevent soil erosion, host a variety of small wild animals 
						and birds. A perfect place to get away from everyday hassles.						
