						<h2>Transport</h2>
						Mboro is 117kms away from the capital Dakar. It's two or three hours drive if you are not stuck in traffic jams. For decades, passengers shuttling between the two cities
						had been taking a big detour via the National Road to avoid the shorter but pothole-riddled "Route des Niayes". Happily it has been recently refurbished and the travel time has now significantly shrunk. 
						To move from Dakar to Mboro, you can take the outlandish senegalese bus called "taxi brousse". But for a quicker painless journey, you'd better opt for the seven-seated car commonly known as "Sept places".
						Do not spend more than 3000 fcfa (5.5$).
						To wander around Mboro, you can catch a "taxi-clando" for 200 fcfa (0.36 $) if your trajectory is not off the only paved main avenue.
						But if ever you want to venture into the sandy streets, walking or hailing the lovely traditional carriage would be more appropriate.   					
