						<h2>Accommodation</h2>
							Obviously Mboro is not a big touristic destination. So don't expect to spend your journey in high-end five stars hotels.<br>
							I assume it's not what your are looking for anyway. From my perspective, the best way to mingle with the locals is to stay within a family proposing a bed-and-breakfast styled service. 
							However the downside is that communication might really be tricky as they are likely not to speak a single world of English. 
							For greater comfort and provided that you can afford it, there are a few inns operated in the isolated district of "Thiérangal" by some Europeans. 
							Up to you to make a choice depending on your budget and travel expectations.<br>
